{"at":804468111.584973,"ticketId":"36","id":"36-19","phase":"decompose","outcome":{"note":{}},"detail":"Here is my report.\n\n---\n\n## DECOMPOSER Report — Issue #36\n\n### What I found\n\n**The implementation is already complete.** Both files have been modified exactly as the issue specifies:\n\n#### `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/ssml\/tags.ts` — function is present (lines 228–232)\n\n```ts\n\/** Look up an attribute definition by tag name and attribute name. *\/\nexport function getAttrDef(tagName: string, attrName: string): SsmlAttrDef | undefined {\n  const def = getTagDef(tagName);\n  if (!def) return undefined;\n  return def.attributes.find((a) => a.name.toLowerCase() === attrName.toLowerCase());\n}\n```\n\n- Reuses `getTagDef` for case-insensitive tag resolution ✓\n- Finds attribute by name case-insensitively via `.toLowerCase()` ✓\n- Returns `SsmlAttrDef | undefined` ✓\n- Returns `undefined` when tag unknown (early return) ✓\n- Returns `undefined` when attribute not found (`find` returns undefined) ✓\n\n#### `apps\/web\/src\/lib\/ssml\/tags.test.ts` — tests are present (lines ~87–109)\n\nFour test cases in a `describe('getAttrDef', ...)` block:\n\n1. **Known attribute** — `getAttrDef('break', 'time')` → returns `{ name: 'time', ... }`\n2. **Case-insensitive match** — `getAttrDef('BREAK', 'TIME')` returns same as exact-case\n3. **Unknown tag** — `getAttrDef('nonexistent', 'time')` → `undefined`\n4. **Known tag, unknown attribute** — `getAttrDef('break', 'nonexistent')` → `undefined`\n\nAll four acceptance criteria are covered.\n\n#### Supporting context\n\n| Fact | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Type** | `SsmlAttrDef` has `name`, `label`, `type`, `options?`, `default?`, `placeholder?`, `required?` |\n| **Existing helper** | `getTagDef(tagName)` — case-insensitive tag lookup via `toLowerCase()` on `SSML_TAGS` array |\n| **Test framework** | `vitest` v4.x, configured in `apps\/web\/vitest.config.ts`, test pattern `src\/**\/*.test.ts`, `jsdom` environment, globals enabled |\n| **Test command** | `npm run test` → `vitest run` |\n| **Callers** | `find_references` reports zero external callers (no UI wiring yet — that's out of scope per the issue) |\n| **Package** | `apps\/web\/package.json` — vitest is in devDependencies |\n\n### Decomposition\n\nSince the work is **already fully implemented**, there is only one deliverable:\n\n**1. Verify and mark complete** — Confirm that `npm run test` passes (the test file already imports `getAttrDef` and contains all four required test cases). No additional code changes are needed.\n\nAlternatively, if this is being re-invoked because a prior build agent implemented it but the workflow expects explicit decomposition before marking done, then the single deliverable is:\n\n**Deliverable A: Function + tests** — a single atomic changeset touching exactly two files (`tags.ts` + `tags.test.ts`), which is already done. The function `getAttrDef` is exported, case-insensitive on both axes, returns `undefined` for missing tag\/attribute, and the tests cover all four scenarios.\n\nNo further decomposition is warranted — this is a single-file, single-function addition with co-located tests."}
